The President has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State now has the power to direct the drawdown of up to $275 million in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under this section to initiate the drawdown. This memorandum has been directed to be published in the Federal Register.